This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on visual recognition tasks. It also involves learning discriminative features and similarity matrices, which are common topics in Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of matrices and optimization techniques suggests that it could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
